  

<h5 id="deer-index-starfish"><a href="https://ellanew.com/2025/10/05/inktober-deer" title="wikilink"><span class="small-caps">⬅️</span> <span class="small-caps">DEER</span></a> · <a href="https://ellanew.com/2025/10/01/inktober-index" title="wikilink"><span class="small-caps">INDEX</span></a> · <a href="https://ellanew.com/2025/10/07/inktober-starfish" title="wikilink"><span class="small-caps">STARFISH</span> <span class="small-caps">➡️</span></a></h5>
<p><img src="https://cdn.blot.im/blog_177bc256f0ee469c998e912e20ece048/_image_cache/0d906fb1-5ffa-4ac4-9112-0d0664b954ff.png" alt="A person holding the string of a heart-shaped balloon is climbing out of a flower that is in the shape of a heart. The person has a small jagged hole over their heart with drops of liquid coming from it. The heart has been pierced and then ripped and split down the middle" width="1280" height="1716"></p>
<p><em>Ink on paper, drawn with non-dominant hand</em></p>
<hr>
<p>Hard times can pierce our hearts, cracking them wide open and leaving us exposed to desolate landscapes and fierce, biting winds.</p>
<p>Peace returns, bit by bit, as we see our wounds for what they are and let them drain. One day, when we are ready, we will know that what we thought was broken was really just the outer layers peeling away. A renewed, more resilient heart is emerging.</p>
<hr>
<p><img src="https://cdn.blot.im/blog_177bc256f0ee469c998e912e20ece048/_image_cache/cd0f0b03-77db-4726-9495-9c725b3ac4f5.png" alt="Coloured drawing of a woman with hair in a bun, wearing shorts and a purple jacket. There are four speech bubbles of varying sizes in the air all around her. Text reads “Over the road conversations with neighbours while kiddies play. Piercing silence to form and deepen friendship. Piercing fabric to mend a hole and redeem a garment." width="1252" height="1660"> <em>Artist: S</em></p>
